The first filter, 'q', takes advantage of a full-text functionality offered by JSONPlaceholder. It is alwaysOn, so it always appears on the screen. The second filter, 'userId', can be added by way of the "add filter" button, located on the top of the list. As it's a , it's already populated with possible users. It can be turned off by the end user.
Filters are "search-as-you-type", meaning that when the user enters new values in the filter form, the list refreshes (via an API request) immediately.

